On March 4, 2016, Shapearl Wells wakes up to a bamming at her door.
It’s the police, telling her that her 22-year-old son, Courtney Copeland, has been shot.
Detectives tell her Courtney drove his BMW to a police station for help.
This week on Intercepted: We air the first episode of Somebody, a new podcast from the Invisible Institute, The Intercept, Topic Studios, and iHeartRadio, in association with Tenderfoot TV.
Somebody explores the racial disparities and turbulent relationship between law enforcement and citizens in one of America’s largest cities.